Date:1/3/2007 11:27:49 AM
From:fp_scientist
Madharry,

Seems to me that TREF likes to keep a low profile (opposite of PDP) and only
releases news on major events. If you contact IR (Sven Engevik +54 11 4814
5556) he will confirm that TREF is already producing 5,000 bopd. Production
will go up significantly as they are taking over new acquisitions with existing
production.

From the presentation at the Pareto Conference (Sep 06):

http://www.trefoil-limited.com/news_presentations.htm

2P reserves are ~24 Mbbl (including their recent acquisitions at Tupungato and
Atamisqui). Market cap of TREF is ~ USD 250M. Compare to PDP: 2P reserves at
~18 Mbbl and market cap of ~USD 800M (w/ warrants & options). There is roughly
a factor 4 in valuation difference.

Of course, with small companies like these, success relies more on the geology
of the fileds and the drilling bit rather than current production or reserves,
but I disagree that TREF is expensive compared to PDP. It is the other way
around, in my view. For more info on TREF reserves, check the Pareto pdf in the
link above.

TREF was focused on Cha&#241;ares Herrados (CH) which has 2P reserves of ~15
Mbbl and then had this home run in Puesto Pozo Cercado (PPC). They are now
focused on PPC which is looking even better than initially thought. TREF has 2
drilling rigs and 2 completion/workover rigs and is trying to get a 3rd
refurbished rig.

The Tupungato and Atamisqui acquisitions will add existing production. TREF
management team is top notch. Also, looks like the PPC discovery could be
extrapolated to the east to Atamisqui. We shall see.

Anyhow, thanks for asking.

fp

Disclaimer: very long TREF.OL
