----
I have an issue with term "impatient investors":

"...Many investors, including me, don't have the patience needed for
traditional value investing. With that in mind, I've devised a screen for
impatient value investors."

My belief is that nobody can be a "value investor" unless they realize they
have to be patient. It's almost built into the term "value investing". If a
buyer is not willing to be patient, he/she must be something else, perhaps
better described as a speculator.
This jmo, of course.
